verbose_text: In the adjusted multivariable conditional logistic regression model, an increased risk of gastric cancer was more likely to have higher odds among those respondents who had a high consumption of processed meat (AOR = 3.99, 95% CI : 0.90-17.66), preferences of a high amount of fats / oil (AOR = 4.64, 95% CI : 1.56-13.72), and preferences of high amounts of salts (AOR = 4.18, 95% CI : 1.30-13.44).
